    </Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <span class="hidden sm:inline">
        Achieving a competitive edge in industrial processes involves adopting cutting-edge practices, particularly in metal surface treatment. The implementation of low-temperature zinc and manganese phosphating techniques offers significant advantages. These environmentally friendly methods not only contribute to energy conservation but also minimise sludge production, aligning with sustainable practices. Specifically designed for structural bridges and rail wagons, low-temperature manganese phosphating enhances the durability and corrosion resistance of these critical infrastructure components.

    </Fragment>
